Necrotizing Enterocolitis (NEC) is a serious condition that primarily affects premature infants, causing inflammation and tissue death in the intestines. The global market for NEC treatment can be segmented based on treatment type, end-user, and region. In terms of treatment type, the market is categorized into surgical treatment, antibiotic treatment, and supportive therapy. Surgical treatment involves the removal of necrotic tissue, while antibiotic treatment focuses on combating infections. Supportive therapy includes measures to stabilize the infant's condition and support recovery. Regarding end-users, the market caters to hospitals, ambulatory surgical centers, specialty clinics, and others. Geographically, the market is segmented into North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, Latin America, and the Middle East and Africa.

